<body>

  <div class="slide bg-charcoal divider-page" data-document-role="page" data-label="— Carousel 01 —">
    <div class="divider-num">01</div>
    <div class="divider-title">5 Signs You&#x27;re Raising a Highly Sensitive Child</div>
  </div>
  <div class="slide bg-charcoal" data-document-role="page" data-label="C01 · Hook">
    <div class="counter">1/10</div>
    <div class="safe safe-top">
      <div class="accent-bar"></div>
      <h1 class="headline hook">5 signs you're raising a <span class="script-word">highly</span> sensitive child</h1>
      <p class="body">The world calls it “too much.” It's not.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="slide bg-offwhite" data-document-role="page" data-label="C01 · Transition">
    <div class="counter">2/10</div>
    <div class="safe">
      <h2 class="headline h-slide">This is not a phase to wait out</h2>
      <hr class="divider-dotted">
      <p class="body">About 1 in 5 kids is wired to feel the world more deeply. Here's how to spot it, so you can stop wondering what's wrong and start seeing what's right.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="slide bg-charcoal" data-document-role="page" data-label="C01 · Tease 1">
    <div class="counter">3/10</div>
    <div class="safe">
      <h2 class="headline h-slide">They <span class="swipe-yellow">notice everything</span></h2>
      <p class="body">The tag in the shirt. Your mood before you say a word.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="slide bg-pink" data-document-role="page" data-label="C01 · Tease 2">
    <div class="counter-dark">4/10</div>
    <div class="safe">
      <h2 class="headline h-slide">Big feelings, and fast</h2>
      <p class="body">Joy is huge. Disappointment is huge. There is no small setting.</p>
      <div class="callout">not too much. just tuned in.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="slide bg-offwhite" data-document-role="page" data-label="C01 · Tease 3">
    <div class="counter">5/10</div>
    <div class="safe">
      <h2 class="headline h-slide">They need to warm up</h2>
      <p class="body">New places and new people take time before they feel safe.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="slide bg-charcoal" data-document-role="page" data-label="C01 · Tease 4">
    <div class="counter">6/10</div>
    <div class="safe">
      <h2 class="headline h-slide">They fall apart after a <span class="swipe-yellow">good day</span></h2>
      <p class="body">Holding it together all day costs them a lot.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="slide bg-offwhite" data-document-role="page" data-label="C01 · Tease 5">
    <div class="counter">7/10</div>
    <div class="safe">
      <h2 class="headline h-slide">They ask deep questions</h2>
      <p class="body">About fairness. About death. About why people hurt.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="slide bg-yellow" data-document-role="page" data-label="C01 · Climax 1">
    <div class="counter">8/10</div>
    <div class="safe">
      <h2 class="headline hook" style="font-size:74px;">None of these are flaws. They are all one thing: a nervous system that feels deeply.</h2>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="slide bg-charcoal" data-document-role="page" data-label="C01 · Climax 2">
    <div class="counter">9/10</div>
    <div class="safe">
      <h2 class="headline hook" style="font-size:74px;">Your child is not too much. They take in more than most people ever notice.</h2>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="slide bg-charcoal" data-document-role="page" data-label="C01 · Action">
    <div class="counter">10/10</div>
    <div class="safe">
      <h2 class="headline h-slide">Comment <span class="highlight-yellow">SIGNS</span> and I'll send you my free Highly Sensitive Child Starter Guide.</h2>
      <p class="body">Save this for the next hard day.</p>
      <p class="creds" style="margin-top:48px;color:var(--light-muted);">Speech Pathologist + Highly Sensitive Person + Homeschooling Mom of 4</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="slide caption-page" data-document-role="page" data-label="C01 · Caption (copy/paste)">
    <div class="caption-flag">Caption — not for posting</div>
    <div class="caption-body">Five signs you&#x27;re raising a highly sensitive child.

They notice everything. They feel big and fast. They need to warm up. They fall apart after a “good” day. They ask deep questions.

None of it means something is wrong. It means their nervous system feels the world deeply. That is not too much. That is tuned in.

Comment SIGNS and I&#x27;ll send you my free Highly Sensitive Child Starter Guide.</div>
    <div class="caption-tags">#highlysensitivechild #sensitivekids #gentleparenting</div>
    <div class="caption-accounts">Tag: none needed</div>
  </div>
  <div class="slide bg-charcoal divider-page" data-document-role="page" data-label="— Carousel 02 —">
    <div class="divider-num">02</div>
    <div class="divider-title">The Driver&#x27;s Ed Story That Explains My Whole Childhood</div>
  </div>
  <div class="slide bg-charcoal" data-document-role="page" data-label="C02 · Hook">
    <div class="counter">1/10</div>
    <div class="safe safe-top">
      <div class="accent-bar"></div>
      <h1 class="headline hook">A driving instructor pulled my mom aside. What he said explained my whole <span class="script-word">childhood</span></h1>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="slide bg-offwhite" data-document-role="page" data-label="C02 · Transition">
    <div class="counter">2/10</div>
    <div class="safe">
      <h2 class="headline h-slide">Sensitivity is not a weak spot</h2>
      <hr class="divider-dotted">
      <p class="body">If you have a child who feels everything, this one is for you. It changed how I see sensitivity for good.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="slide bg-charcoal" data-document-role="page" data-label="C02 · Tease 1">
    <div class="counter">3/10</div>
    <div class="safe">
      <h2 class="headline h-slide">Growing up, I felt like the odd one</h2>
      <p class="body">I cried easily. I noticed things no one else did.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="slide bg-pink" data-document-role="page" data-label="C02 · Tease 2">
    <div class="counter-dark">4/10</div>
    <div class="safe">
      <h2 class="headline h-slide">People said I was too sensitive</h2>
      <p class="body">I believed them. I thought something was off with me.</p>
      <div class="callout">the noticing was never the problem.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="slide bg-offwhite" data-document-role="page" data-label="C02 · Tease 3">
    <div class="counter">5/10</div>
    <div class="safe">
      <h2 class="headline h-slide">Then I took driver's ed</h2>
      <p class="body">I checked every mirror. I saw every car before it moved.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="slide bg-charcoal" data-document-role="page" data-label="C02 · Tease 4">
    <div class="counter">6/10</div>
    <div class="safe">
      <h2 class="headline h-slide">My instructor had taught for <span class="swipe-yellow">15 years</span></h2>
      <p class="body">One day he walked up to my mom in the parking lot.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="slide bg-offwhite" data-document-role="page" data-label="C02 · Tease 5">
    <div class="counter">7/10</div>
    <div class="safe">
      <h2 class="headline h-slide">“I've never told a parent this. She's the best driver I've ever had.”</h2>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="slide bg-yellow" data-document-role="page" data-label="C02 · Climax 1">
    <div class="counter">8/10</div>
    <div class="safe">
      <h2 class="headline hook" style="font-size:74px;">The thing that made me too sensitive was the same thing that kept me safe. I noticed everything.</h2>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="slide bg-charcoal" data-document-role="page" data-label="C02 · Climax 2">
    <div class="counter">9/10</div>
    <div class="safe">
      <h2 class="headline hook" style="font-size:74px;">Your sensitive kid isn't behind. They see a world most people tune out.</h2>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="slide bg-charcoal" data-document-role="page" data-label="C02 · Action">
    <div class="counter">10/10</div>
    <div class="safe">
      <h2 class="headline h-slide">Comment <span class="highlight-yellow">DRIVER</span> and I'll send you my free Highly Sensitive Child Starter Guide.</h2>
      <p class="body">Follow for more.</p>
      <p class="creds" style="margin-top:48px;color:var(--light-muted);">Speech Pathologist + Highly Sensitive Person + Homeschooling Mom of 4</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="slide caption-page" data-document-role="page" data-label="C02 · Caption (copy/paste)">
    <div class="caption-flag">Caption — not for posting</div>
    <div class="caption-body">A driving instructor pulled my mom aside after class. He had taught for over 15 years. He said, “I&#x27;ve never told a parent this before. She&#x27;s the best driver I&#x27;ve ever had.”

For years I&#x27;d been called too sensitive. But the same wiring that made me notice every feeling made me notice every car on the road.

Your sensitive kid isn&#x27;t behind. They are awake to a world most people miss.

