    <div class="caption-accounts">Tag: none needed</div>
  </div>
  <div class="slide bg-charcoal divider-page" data-document-role="page" data-label="— Carousel 04 —">
    <div class="divider-num">04</div>
    <div class="divider-title">Stop Saying “You&#x27;re Okay” to a Sensitive Child</div>
  </div>
  <div class="slide bg-charcoal" data-document-role="page" data-label="C04 · Hook">
    <div class="counter">1/10</div>
    <div class="safe safe-top">
      <div class="accent-bar"></div>
      <h1 class="headline hook">“You're okay.” It sounds kind. To a sensitive child, it quietly shuts them <span class="script-word">down</span></h1>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="slide bg-offwhite" data-document-role="page" data-label="C04 · Transition">
    <div class="counter">2/10</div>
    <div class="safe">
      <h2 class="headline h-slide">Small words carry big messages</h2>
      <hr class="divider-dotted">
      <p class="body">The words we reach for by habit can teach kids to hide feelings. Here's what to say instead.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="slide bg-charcoal" data-document-role="page" data-label="C04 · Tease 1">
    <div class="counter">3/10</div>
    <div class="safe">
      <h2 class="headline h-slide">They hear something else</h2>
      <p class="body">When you say “you're okay,” they hear: what I feel is wrong. So they bottle it.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="slide bg-pink" data-document-role="page" data-label="C04 · Tease 2">
    <div class="counter-dark">4/10</div>
    <div class="safe">
      <h2 class="headline h-slide">Sensitive kids feel first</h2>
      <p class="body">The feeling has to be seen before it can settle. Thinking comes later.</p>
      <div class="callout">feel it with them first.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="slide bg-offwhite" data-document-role="page" data-label="C04 · Tease 3">
    <div class="counter">5/10</div>
    <div class="safe">
      <h2 class="headline h-slide">Try: “That was a lot. <span class="underline-pink">I'm right here.</span>”</h2>
      <p class="body">You name it, and you stay.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="slide bg-charcoal" data-document-role="page" data-label="C04 · Tease 4">
    <div class="counter">6/10</div>
    <div class="safe">
      <h2 class="headline h-slide">Try: “You're allowed to feel this. <span class="swipe-yellow">I've got you.</span>”</h2>
      <p class="body">Safety comes before the fix.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="slide bg-offwhite" data-document-role="page" data-label="C04 · Tease 5">
    <div class="counter">7/10</div>
    <div class="safe">
      <h2 class="headline h-slide">You are not feeding the meltdown</h2>
      <p class="body">You are helping their body come back down.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="slide bg-yellow" data-document-role="page" data-label="C04 · Climax 1">
    <div class="counter">8/10</div>
    <div class="safe">
      <h2 class="headline hook" style="font-size:74px;">Kids don't calm down by being told to. They calm down by being felt with.</h2>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="slide bg-charcoal" data-document-role="page" data-label="C04 · Climax 2">
    <div class="counter">9/10</div>
    <div class="safe">
      <h2 class="headline hook" style="font-size:74px;">The goal isn't a child who stops crying fast. It's one who trusts you with the hard stuff.</h2>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="slide bg-charcoal" data-document-role="page" data-label="C04 · Action">
    <div class="counter">10/10</div>
    <div class="safe">
      <h2 class="headline h-slide">Comment <span class="highlight-yellow">WORDS</span> and I'll send you my free Highly Sensitive Child Starter Guide.</h2>
      <p class="body">Share with a parent who needs it.</p>
      <p class="creds" style="margin-top:48px;color:var(--light-muted);">Speech Pathologist + Highly Sensitive Person + Homeschooling Mom of 4</p>
    </div>
  </div>
